      "id": "1ktfo1dcq",
      "questionNumber": 1,
      "questionText": "A zener diode of power rating 2W is to be used as a voltage regulator. If the zener diode has a breakdown of 10 V and it has to regulate voltage fluctuated between 6 V and 14 V, the value of R<sub>s</sub> for safe operation should be ___________ $$\\Omega$$.<br><br><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktqsvjv2/1cb1665b-03f9-4386-b1a7-3f58d4a982d3/683bc6e0-190d-11ec-9e1c-4f8f7e7dad5b/file-1ktqsvjv3.jpeg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 27th August Evening Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 123 English\">",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "semiconductor-and-p-n-junction-diode",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "When unregulated voltage is 14 V voltage across zener diode must be 10 V. So potential difference across resistor $$\\Delta$$V<sub>Rs</sub> = 4V<br><br>and P<sub>zener</sub> = 2W<br><br>VI = 2<br><br>I = $${2 \\over {10}}$$ = 0.2 A<br><br>$$\\Delta$$V<sub>Rs</sub> = I R<sub>s</sub><br><br>4 $$\\times$$ 0.2 R<sub>s</sub> $$\\Rightarrow$$ R<sub>s</sub> = $${40 \\over {2}}$$ = 20$$\\Omega$$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
