    {
      "id": "HvowV4O87x8yHivlUq3rsa0w2w9jwzgxe4x",
      "questionNumber": 6,
      "questionText": "The figure represents a voltage regulator circuit using a Zener diode. The breakdown voltage of the Zener\ndiode is 6 V and the load resistance is, R<sub>L</sub> = 4k$$\\Omega $$. The series resistance of the circuit is R<sub>i</sub>\n = 1 k$$\\Omega $$. If the\nbattery voltage V<sub>B</sub> varies from 8 V to 16 V, what are the minimum and maximum values of the current\nthrough Zener diode?\n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/3rsa0w2w9jwzguc6e/cb998e85-7959-4c89-a579-e97fd92255d4/43475c60-907e-11e9-86c1-73f7f991b766/file-3rsa0w2w9jwzguc6f.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th April Evening Slot Physics - Semiconductor Question 181 English\">",
      "options": [
        "0.5 mA; 8.5 mA",
        "1.5 mA; 8.5 mA",
        "1 mA; 8.5 mA",
        "0.5 mA; 6 mA"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "semiconductor-and-p-n-junction-diode",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7kejek19ozgxa/9b5bb61f-eaa5-4ba5-b5a4-9a14d08a2b8b/cf08c8e0-e54e-11e9-a7bc-b7b08ce8d541/file-7kejek19ozgxb-443w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 10th April Evening Slot Physics - Semiconductor Question 181 English Explanation\">\nV<sub>breakdwon</sub> = 6V, RL = 4k$$\\Omega $$, R<sub>i</sub> = 1 k$$\\Omega $$<br><br>\n$${i_L} = {6 \\over 4} \\times {10^{ - 3}} = 1.5 \\times {10^{ - 3}} = 1.5\\,mA$$<br><br>\ni<sub>i</sub> = 2 × 10<sup>–3</sup><br>\ni = i<sub>1</sub> – i<sub>L</sub> = 0.5 mA – minimum current<br><br>\ni<sub>i</sub> = 10 × 10<sup>–3</sup> = 10 mA<br>\ni<sub>max</sub> = 8.5 mA \n",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
