    {
      "id": "uFS8QCqEbkcvqyadMjiw0",
      "questionNumber": 9,
      "questionText": "An NPN transistor is used in common emitter\nconfiguration as an amplifier with 1 k$$\\Omega $$ load\nresistance. Signal voltage of 10 mV is applied\nacross the base-emitter. This produces a 3 mA\nchange in the collector current and 15μA\nchange in the base current of the amplifier. The\ninput resistance and voltage gain are :",
      "options": [
        "0.67 kW, 200",
        "0.33 kW, 1.5",
        "0.67 kW, 300",
        "0.33 kW, 300"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "transistors",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Input current = 15 × 10<sup>–6</sup><br><br>\nOutput current = 3 × 10<sup>–3</sup><br><br>\nResistance out put = 1000<br><br>\nV<sub>input</sub> = 10 × 10<sup>–3</sup><br><br>\nNow V<sub>input</sub> = r<sub>input</sub> × i<sub>input</sub><br><br>\n10 × 10<sup>–3</sup> = r<sub>input</sub> × 15 × 10<sup>–6</sup><br><br>\nr<sub>input</sub> = $${{2000} \\over 3} = 0.67\\,K\\Omega $$<br><br>\nVoltage gain = $${{{V_{output}}} \\over {{V_{input}}}} = {{1000 \\times 3 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}} \\over {10 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}} = 300$$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "1l54vrih4",
      "questionNumber": 10,
      "questionText": "<p>A potential barrier of 0.4 V exists across a p-n junction. An electron enters the junction from the n-side with a speed of 6.0 $$\\times$$ 10<sup>5</sup> ms<sup>$$-$$1</sup>. The speed with which electron enters the p side will be $${x \\over 3} \\times {10^5}$$ ms<sup>$$-$$1</sup> the value of x is _____________.</p>\n<p>(Given mass of electron = 9 $$\\times$$ 10<sup>$$-$$31</sup> kg, charge on electron = 1.6 $$\\times$$ 10<sup>$$-$$19</sup> C.)</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "semiconductor-and-p-n-junction-diode",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Conserving energy,</p>\n<p>$${1 \\over 2}m{v^2} = {1 \\over 2}m{(6 \\times {10^5})^2} - 0.4\\,eV$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow v = \\sqrt {{{(6 \\times {{10}^5})}^2} - {{2 \\times 1.6 \\times {{10}^{ - 19}} \\times 0.4} \\over {9 \\times {{10}^{ - 31}}}}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\sqrt {36 \\times {{10}^{10}} - {{1.28} \\over 9} \\times {{10}^{12}}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow v = {{14} \\over 3} \\times {10^5}$$ m/s</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow x = 14$$</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
